  "prompt": "How does flitto app make money?",
  "response": "Flitto is a translation and crowd-sourcing platform that connects users needing translation services with multilingual contributors. The app has various ways to generate revenue:\n\n1. **Translation Services**: Flitto allows businesses and individuals to request translations for text, audio, and images. It charges clients a fee for these services, which can vary based on the complexity and length of the content.\n\n2. **Crowd-Sourcing Model**: Flitto utilizes a crowd-sourcing model, where users can earn rewards by contributing translations. This model helps keep operational costs lower while still providing quality translations, allowing Flitto to maintain competitive pricing for end-users.\n\n3. **Subscription Plans**: Flitto may offer subscription plans to businesses that require regular translation services, providing a steady revenue stream.\n\n4. **Advertising**: The app might implement advertising to monetize traffic and user engagement on its platform.\n\n5. **Premium Features**: Flitto could offer premium features or enhanced services for a fee, such as expedited translations or access to additional languages.\n\nBy leveraging a mix of these strategies, Flitto can effectively monetize its platform while providing valuable services to users in need of translation.",
